Of the 146 patients with NPC who received penpulimab-kcqx in combination with either cisplatin or carboplatin and gemcitabine, 15 (10%) were 65 years or older and 1 (0.7%) was 75 years or older. Clinical studies did not include a sufficient number of patients aged 65 years or older to determine differences in safety or effectiveness compared to younger patients [see

                           Adverse Reactions (6)
                           ].

o Advise patients that immune-mediated adverse reactions can occur and may involve any organ system, and to contact their healthcare provider immediately for any new or worsening signs or symptoms 
  [see Warnings and Precautions (5.1) 
                     ].
